Program: The Forum
Title: Rewilding
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p026lnqs
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 22 Sep 2014
From the release of captive species to their natural habitats, to restoring ecosystems in rural and urban areas, to “rewilding the child”, Tim Marlow explores ideas about rewilding. With environmentalist and writer George Monbiot, Frans Schepers from Rewilding Europe and Joan Nassauer Professor of Landscape Architecture at the University of Michigan. (Photo: The Gray Wolf; the species was reintroduced to Yellowstone National Park, USA in 1995. Credit: AP) Show less